Package: bayesgm
Title: R Interface to the Python 'bayesgm' Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Qiao", "Liu", email = "qiao.liu@yale.edu", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")))
Description: Provides an R interface to the Python 'bayesgm' toolkit through
    'reticulate'. The package exposes lightweight R wrappers around the
    Python 'CausalBGM' and 'BGM' APIs so R users can configure models,
    fit them from R, and obtain causal or generative-model predictions
    without leaving the R workflow.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/liuq-lab/bayesgm
BugReports: https://github.com/liuq-lab/bayesgm/issues
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.9), Python package 'bayesgm'
Imports:
    R6,
    reticulate
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Config/testthat/edition: 3
